<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-15T22:13:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-15T22:13:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/826</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-16T12:00:00+08:47"><hi rend="italic">December 16, 1917, 12 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 16, 3.45
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Japanese troops have not arrived here and none dispatched as far as I
                                can learn although many seem expect and some now even hope for their
                                coming.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_CJK1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>